# No "thesis" wording

OpenPVScope is a product. Do **not** refer to a thesis in:

- UI copy, tooltips, labels, console/activity logs
- User-visible API messages, `pipeline_rev`, health payloads shown to operators
- Comments or docstrings that ship in product code (prefer "legacy suite", "previous app", or "old code")

When comparing behavior, say **old code** / **legacy suite**, not thesis.

Internal planning or private notes may mention academic origin only if the user asks; never put that language into the product surface.
